This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    requestType - The type of request to perform.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

This flow checks Approval Status column based on input parameters Approval Status, “Approved”, and Comments. If column does not match the value, call Set_SLS_Flag module to return “Withdrawn” flag.

Inputs\:
   approvalStatus\:The approvalStatus Value
   approvalValue \: By default the value is set to“Accepted”
   flagValue \:By default the value is set to “Not to be loaded”



Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.

b78d7d78-27c7-4dbc-b99b-bca7d413e940.description=
This is the check phase of pricing workflow. it validates all the loan and decides whether to go to update phase of notify phase.

Inputs\:
   emailId - Id of the email to process

Outputs\:
accountFlag	- account flag (rework or null)
accountNumbers - loan account numbers
approvalFlag	- indicates approval value
approvedBy - incates who has approved.
automationFailureFlag - automation failure flag
customerZNumber - Z number of cutomer.
errorMessage - captured error message
extraAttachmentFlag - indicate extra attachment flag
noAttachmentFlag - indicates no attachment
pconState - pcon value
processFlag - process flag
RateFinderRequestorEmailAddr - rate finder requestor email ID
requestorName - requestor name
requestType - request type
